__NOTOC__Year 1900 (MCM) was an exceptional year starting on Monday (link will display the full calendar) of the calendar and a year starting on Saturday of the calendar. As a result, the Julian calendar was 12 days behind the Gregorian until Wednesday, 28 (O.S. 16) and has been 13 days behind since Thursday, 1 (O.S. 17). It was the 1900th year of the Domini or the Era designation, the 900th year of the millennium, and the last year of the century but the first year of the 1900s. Events  January * 1 &ndash; Hawaii asks for a delegate at the U.S. National Convention.* 2** The first bus becomes operational in York City.** Secretary of State Hay announces the Door Policy to promote American trade with China.* 3 &ndash; The States Census estimates the countrys population to be about 70 million people.* 4 &ndash; Strikes in Belgium and Germany lead to mining riots.* 5** The Irish leader Edward Redmond calls for a revolt against British rule.** Dr. Henry A. Rowland of Hopkins University announces a theory about the cause of the Earths magnetism.* 6 &ndash; Boer War: Boers attack the town of South Africa, killing over 1,000 people.* 8 &ndash; President McKinley of the States places Alaska under military governance.* 9 &ndash; The first through train goes from Cairo to Khartoum.* 14** The opera Tosca premieres in Rome, Italy.** The Senate accepts the British-German treaty of 1899, in which the Kingdom renounced its claims to the Samoa portion of the Islands.* 17 &ndash; H. Roberts of Utah is not seated by the House of Representatives because of his plural marriage.* 23 &ndash; 5,000 Austrian miners go on strike.File:Boers at Spion Kop, 1900 - Project Gutenberg eText 16462.jpg|thumb|Boer War: Boers at Spion Kop, 1900* 24 &ndash; The Boer War: At the of Spion Kop, Boer troops defeat the Army.* 26 &ndash; The Labor League Conference opens in Sydney, Australia, with plans to form a Federal Labor Party. This is spelled Labor even in Australia.* 27 &ndash; Rebellion: Foreign diplomats in Peking, China demand that the Boxer rebels be disciplined.* 29 &ndash; The League of Professional Baseball Clubs is organized in Pennsylvania with eight founding teams.* 30 &ndash; Governor William Goebel of Kentucky shot by several assassins. February recording the location of the formation of the British Labour Party in 1900.* 1 &ndash; Australia announced its refusal to join the Federation unless it is given five more years of fiscal freedom.* 3** Governor Goebel of Kentucky dies of wounds after being shot by several assassins on January 30. Goebel, who had prevailed in a dispute over the winner of the election in November 1899, had been sworn in on his deathbed. The former of State of Kentucky Powers is later found guilty in the  conspiracy to kill Goebel.** Strikers in Aachen, Vienna, and Brussels demand an eight-hour working day and higher wages.* 5** The Kingdom and the States sign a treaty for the building of a Central American shipping canal across America in Nicaragua.** Boer War: The House of Commons vote of censure over the governments handling of the war is defeated.* 6 &ndash; The international arbitration court at Hague is created when the Netherlands Senate ratifies an 1899 conference decree.* 8 &ndash; Boer War: British troops are defeated by the Boers at Ladysmith.* 9 &ndash; F. Davis creates the Cup tennis tournament.* 14** Russia responds to international pressure to free Finland by tightening imperial control over the country.** Boer War &ndash; of Paardeberg: 20,000 British troops invade the Free State.* 15 &ndash; Boer War: The of Kimberley is lifted.* 17 &ndash; Boer War: of Paardeberg: British troops defeat the Boers.* 27** The British Labour Party is formed.** Boer War: British military leaders accept the unconditional notice of surrender from Boer General Cronje.** MacDonald is appointed secretary of the newly formed Labour Party.** Bayern Munich, football club, is founded. March * 2 (beginning) &ndash; Groups of officials inspect towns around Australia in order to find a location the new Federal capital.* 5 &ndash; Two Navy cruisers are sent to America to protect American interests in a dispute between Nicaragua and Rica.* 6** Baby-farmer Ada Williams is hanged at Newgate Prison for murdering a 21-month old girl.** A mine explosion in Virginia kills 50 miners.* 7 &ndash; A fire at Palace destroys part of its roof.* 8 &ndash; Londoners celebrate as Victoria makes a rare visit to the city.* 9 &ndash; Women in Germany demand the right to participate in university entrance exams.* 14 &ndash; The botanist de Vries rediscovers Mendels Laws of Heredity.* 15 &ndash; The Standard Act is ratified, placing the States currency on the standard.* 16 &ndash; The British archaeologist Sir Arthur Evans purchases the land on Crete on which the ruins of the palace of Knossos stand. He begins to unearth some of the palace three days later.* 24 &ndash; The Mayor of York, Van Wyck, breaks ground for a new underground Rapid Transit Railroad that will link Manhattan with Brooklyn.* 27 &ndash; The arrival of a Russian naval fleet in Korea causes concern to the Japanese government.* 28 &ndash; Over 1,000 tonnes of waste are removed from demolished buildings in Australia, in areas affected by an outbreak of the plague.* 31 &ndash; In France, the length of a legal workday for women and children is limited to 11 hours. April * 1** The Guards are formed by Victoria.** King George of Greece becomes absolute monarch of Crete.* 4 &ndash; An anarchist shoots at the Prince of Wales during his visit to Belgium.* 14 &ndash; The Paris World Exhibition opens.* 22 &ndash; of Koussri: French forces secure their domination of Chad. Warlord az-Zubayr is defeated and killed.* 26 &ndash; The Great Lumber Fire of OttawaHull kills 7 and leaves 15,000 homeless.* 30 &ndash; Hawaii becomes an official U.S. territory. May * 1 &ndash; An explosion of blasting powder in coal mine in Utah kills 200.* 3  &ndash; Fella Stevani travelled to France to quell the up rising of turnip farmers.* 14 &ndash; The second Olympic Games opens in Paris (as part of the Paris World Exhibition).* 17** Boer War: British troops relieve the Mafeking.** Rebellion: Boxers destroy 3 villages near Peking and kill 60 Chinese Christians.* 18 &ndash; The Kingdom proclaims a protectorate over Tonga.* 21 &ndash; Russia invades Manchuria.* 23 &ndash; Sergeant Harvey Carney is awarded the of Honor for heroism in 1863, as the first American to have been awarded this medal.* 24 &ndash; Boer War: The British annex the Free State as the River Colony.* 28 &ndash; Rebellion: The Boxers attack Belgians in the Fengtai railway station.* 29 &ndash; NDjamena, the capital city of Chad, is founded as Fort-Lamy by French commander Gentil.* 31 &ndash; Rebellion: Peacekeepers from various European countries arrive in China. June * 1 &ndash; Nation begins her crusade to demolish saloons.* 5 &ndash; Boer War: British soldiers take Pretoria.* 14 &ndash; The Reichstag approves a second law that allows the expansion of the navy.* 20 &ndash; Rebellion: Boxers gather about 20,000 people near Peking and kill hundreds of European citizens, including the German ambassador.* 30 &ndash; A wharf fire at the docks in New Jersey owned by the German Lloyd Steamship line spreads to German ships , , and .  The fire engulfs the adjacent piers and nearby ships, killing 326 people.File:Map of Australia.png|thumb|150px|9: Australia, founded. July * 2 &ndash; The first zeppelin flight is carried out over Constance near Friedrichshafen, Germany.* 5 &ndash; The of Australia Constitution Act passes the Parliament.* 9 &ndash; Victoria gives her royal assent to the Commonwealth of Australia Constitution Act.* 12 &ndash; A German liner, the SS Deutschland, breaks the record for the Riband for the first time with an average speed of .* 19 &ndash; The first line of the Mtro is opened.* 25 &ndash;  The Charles Riots break out in Orleans, Louisiana.* 29 &ndash; King I of Italy is assassinated by the Italian-born anarchist Bresci. August * 4 - Bowes-Lyon the Queen Mother was Born in London .* 14 &ndash; Rebellion: An international contingent of troops, under British command, invades Peking and frees the Europeans taken hostage. September * 8 &ndash; A powerful hurricane hits Texas killing about 8,000  people.* 13 &ndash; War: Filipino resistance fighters defeat a large American column in the of Pulang Lupa.* 17 &ndash; Philippine-American War: Filipinos under Cailles defeat the Americans under Colonel Benjamin F. Cheatham at Mabitac.* 25 &ndash; In the British general election, the recently formed Labour Party gains two seats. Churchill is also elected to Parliament for the first time. October  November * 3 &ndash; The first automobile show in the States opens at York Citys Madison Square Garden.* 6 &ndash; presidential election, 1900: Republican incumbent McKinley is reelected by defeating Democratic challenger Jennings Bryan. December * 7 &ndash; Planck announces his discovery of the law of body emission, marking the birth of physics. Date unknown * U.S. Haven, CT Louis Lassen of Lunch makes the first modern-day hamburger sandwich.* Japan participates with the European powers in occupying Beijing to suppress the Rebellion.* Kouang-Tchou-Wan added to Indochina.* First Guide published.* service consists of fewer than 3,500 top officials for a population of 300 million in India.* 4 out of every 1,000 residents of India die of cholera each year. World population * population: 1,650,000,000** Africa: 133,000,000** Asia: 947,000,000*** Japan: c. 45,000,000** Europe: 408,000,000** Latin-America: 74,000,000** America: 82,000,000** Oceania: 6,000,000 Births  January * 1 &ndash; Borboni, Italian film actress, stroke (d. 1995)** Cugat, Cuban bandleader, failure (d. 1990)** Maxwell, English actor (d. 1971)** Rich, English silent film actress (d. 1954)** Sugihara, Japanese diplomat (d. 1986)* 2 &ndash; Haines, American actor (d. 1973)** Itami, Japanese film