This is a list of planned cities (sometimes known as planned communities or towns) by country. Additions to this list should be cities whose overall form (as opposed to individual neighborhoods or expansions) has been determined in large part in advance on a drawing board, or which were planned to a degree which is unusual for their time and place.Argentina*Plata  Buenos Aires*La Punta  San Luis*Jardn Lomas del Palomar  Buenos AiresAustralia*Adelaide  South Australia*Canberra  Australian Capital Territory*Churchill  Victoria*Eaglemont  Victoria*Griffith  New South Wales*Inala  Queensland*Leeton  New South Wales*Melbourne  Victoria*Mildura  Victoria*Monarto  South Australia (never built)*Polis  South Australia (never built)*Palmerston  Northern Territory*Garden City  Victoria*Yallourn  VictoriaAustria*Plten http://www.st-poelten.gv.at/Belarus*Novopolotsk (plan developed in 1958) http://www.2goroda.by/main.aspx?formcontent&file472*Soligorsk (construction began in 1958)Belgium*Louvain-la-NeuveBelize*BelmopanBrazil*Aracaju*Belmonte, Santa Catarina State*Horizonte (inaugurated in 1897)*Vista, Roraima*Braslia*Canarana - Mato Grosso State*Cataguases (most of the towns central areas were developed according to a plan, though the rest of the town has since grown randomly)*Curitiba*Erechim*Fordlndia A dream of Henry Ford, now abandoned*Goinia*Valadares (1915)*Solteira*Londrina*Maring*Palmas*de Contas http://www.google.com/search?qcache:N2S6rA9u3y8J:www.ufogenesis.com.br/ufoturismo/chapada_diamantina.htm+%22%C3%A9+uma+cidade+planejada%22&hlpt-BR&glbr&ctclnk&cd10&clientfirefox-a*Bahia *Sinop*do Leste - Mato Grosso State*Sorriso - Mato Grosso State*Teresina (The first one, inaugurated in 1852 from Oeiras)Botswana*GaboroneBurma*NaypyidawCanadaPlanned cities of Eastern Canada are notable.  In Western Canada, however, virtually all cities and towns created after the 1870 Dominion Lands Act (the majority of all such cities) were planned.  Most were railway towns, surveyed and subdivided by the powerful railway companies. For example, both Hat, Alberta and Current, Saskatchewan were founded by the CPR during construction of the main transcontinental line.  The only cities in Western Canada that grew organically were those, usually founded before 1870, that grew up around fur trade forts, police outposts, or missions.*Ontario*Ontario, now a part of Brampton, Ontario*Nova Scotia (failed)*Brook, Newfoundland*River, Ontario*Mills, now a part of Toronto*Mills, part of Mississauga*Quebec*Quebec*Ontario*Falls-Windsor, Newfoundland*Kapuskasing, Ontario*British Columbia*Royal, Quebec*Westminster, British Columbia, designed by Richard Clements Moody of the Royal Engineers to be the capital of the Colony of British Columbia. *Oromocto, New Brunswick*Manitoba*Manitoba*Ontario (failed)*Ridge, British Columbia*OntarioChile*Salvador, Chile mining cityCzech Republic*Havov*ZlnDenmark*restadEstonia*Paldiski*VruFinland*Helsinki*Tapiola, Espoo http://english.espoo.fi//default.asp?path32373*Rovaniemi http://www.rovaniemi.fi/Intro.iw3?langen*HaminaFrance*Near Paris: **Cergy-Pontoise,  http://www.ville-cergy.fr/**Marne-la-Valle, http://www.san-valmaubuee.fr**Snart, http://www.san-senart.fr**vry,http://www.sanevry.fr** en Yvelines  http://www.san-sqy.fr*Near Lille: dAscq*Near Lyon: dAbeau*Near Marseille: de lEtang de Berre*Near Rouen: de Reuil*Saltworks at Arc-et-Senans*Fos http://www.san-vnf.fr*Neuf-Brisach*VersaillesGermany*Bremerhaven http://www.bremerhaven.de*Eisenhttenstadt*Freudenstadt*Glckstadt*Karlsruhe http://www.karlsruhe.de*Ludwigslust*Mannheim*Putbus*Salzgitter*Germania (never built)*Wilhelmshaven*WolfsburgHong Kong*Tsuen Wan*Sha Tin *Tuen Mun *Tai Po *Fanling - Sheung Shui *Yuen Long *Tseung Kwan O *Tin Shui Wai *North Lantau (Tung Chung - Tai Ho)*East New Territories New Development Area*West New Territories New Development AreaHungary*Dunajvros http://www.dunaujvaros.hu*Kazincbarcika http://www.kazincbarcika.hu*Oroszlny http://www.oroszlany.hu*Petfibnya